caption: Great service..nice bar and friendly staff..good food
The pad thai was really bland thats supposed to be the bread and butter dish. Sukho thai is bettter in my opinion.
I wish, I could cook this well!!!

Lad na, just order it Some of the stuff here is too sugary, like the tom kha or the papaya salad, but the drunken noodle is perfect in terms of noodle texture and the gravy, also the beef is tender but still has bite and the bit of chili and vinegar they give on the side gives it just enough kick and acidity to be perfect
Great food and great service.
Garbage
Love this restaurant. Great food and atmosphere. Right in the heart of New Orleans. Friendly staff. Great place for family dinner or a business meeting.
The food was delicious, the service outstanding, and the best prices in town!

Second time I've  been burned at this place was today. I ordered a lunch special Massaman Curry with tofu instead of beef. He kept asking me if i wanted vegetables and I specifically said, only how it comes, not extra vegetables, just replace the beef with tofu. Of course when I get the food instead of Massaman curry I get some kind of spice-less sweet curry type vegetable mixture with like 2 pieces of plain tofu and rice. It was literally a mixture of canned vegetables like canned baby corn and canned mushrooms (gross) with pea pods and celery. Like what the hell is this? Plus, it tastes gross. Doesn't even taste like curry. On top of that, when they rang me up my total was nearly $20 for the order of lunch special curry and an order or spring roles (which btw were also disgusting and tasted like they came straight out of the freezer), when online the lunch special prices were less than what they charged me for each item. I pointed this out and he didn't even offer to refund my money for the difference. What a rip off. Nasty food made wrong on top of being over charged. I dont even know why I agreed to pay for my meal tbh. People, avoid this place and go to Sudkho Thai instead, its WAY better.

I've been eating at Thai restaurants around New Orleans for most of my life, and my opinion, this is the best in the city! The owner is extremely warm and caring and we always get excellent service. They have a great range of authentic Thai food - I'd suggest going around lunch time for some Pad Thai, Musaman curry, or Panang Fish with crawfish. Their shrimp dumplings and spring rolls are my favorite appetizers.
Great Authentic Thai Restaurant
Best tom yam soup in the city !!!!
Very yummy!

I’m a regular orderer of Singha Thai via Postmates and I absolutely love it!  It’s rare that to go/delivery food is the same quality as eating at a restaurant, but somehow, Singha Thai pulls it off.  It no doubt has something to do with fresh ingredients, you can absolutely tell.  See y’all next week!

Pretty nice thai food spot!  The papaya salad had a nice twist to it with the fresh shrimp and onions (the som tam I'm used to has dried shrimp).  I personally would have preferred more spice, but the food was good nonetheless!
Love this place!

Fish cakes were good, the Lad Na was also good .  This is next to the pho restauraunt on Baronne.  Fast and flavorful.  The noodles were thicker then pho rice noodle.  Will need to go again and I do recommend

Food was delicious, but there was a lady who was seated nearby that kept coughing and coughing obnoxiously without covering her mouth..it was pretty digusting and unappetizing  for the other seated guests.
Ok

I accidentally ordered from here the second time because I couldn't remember if this was the place I ordered from before that I hated! And yes! The food is not a mistake, it really is consistently that bad. I would not, I repeated NOT get food from here. The meat is funky and the soup has tomato’s and the curry is bland, the pad Thai seemed like it was reheated and all the noodles were broken into tiny pieces... yeah this place should not be in business.
Really nice food, good taste
Modest decor, but tasty curry.
Quiet, polite staff, food was great
Everything was wonderful! The best Thai!
food is way overpriced and some of the worst Thai food I've ever had. This one small bowl of green curry is NOT worth 15$. Save yourself the disappointnent and save your wallet.
I visit this place a lot since I work nearby. I must say their customer service is always excellent and they keep the spot neat all the time. Rates are affordable and they serve big portions.
Enjoyed the food.  If u like spicy u need to ask them to heat it up.  There were 11 of us and we were all very satisfied.
Great food and service, this place also has a bar for those interested having a drink.
This is not really Thai food at all. The curry taste sweet and fried rice as well. If you really need some Asia Food, you could come.

Was visiting New Orleans for vacation. I always go with Thai food wherever I travel. Ordered takeout from here. By far the worst thai I have ever had. Threw most of it away. Would not recommend to anyone.
Good location, good taste however nothing spectacular about the food. I have had better Thai food at other places.  Give it a try.  Visited - Nov Ordered - Veg red curry and veg Pad see mow
The best food I had in New Orleans, really good  chai ice tea. Amazing service
Pretty bland for Thai food
Good food, and good service.
Best Thai in all of NOLA

I understand that not every Thai restaurant I go to is going to be amazing.  But I have to admit being very disappointed in the food here.  Ordered a appetizer (spring roll) and a yellow curry. Extremely salty.  Sauce was barely edible with the curry due to the over salting and I didn’t pick up any anything authentic in terms of flavor with the rolls.  It’s in the city district, ok.   Attracts business people alike to come at lunch and I figure they don’t like things too spicy or foreign to their taste buds.  But I was hoping to go in and get something ethnic and true to Thai flavors.
Timing on google is incorrect! Was closed and staff was rude
Great food!

The staff was friendly and the food was quite cheap for the quality of food. I like spicy curry, but the chicken curry I got was not spicy. The server didn’t ask me for a level of spice, so I just assumed it would spicy. The pad thai was also tasty with lots of shrimp and chicken. Still, good food, good price, will be back and ask for my spice.
The place was deliciousas . *
Love this place.  They have great dri is specials .

I definitely wouldn't come here again. I was quite disappointed, unfortunately. I ordered pad thai that was dry and didn't have even the slightest hint of peanut, or flavor of any kind. The fresh rolls were mostly just lettuce. The pad thai was really inedible. :(

One of the only Thai restaurants in the city open on Monday. Nothing overly exciting about the dining space but the food is consistently good. The restaurant offers gender neutral restroom facilities.

Not satisfied. 1. I ordered to go and asked to prepare without mushrooms, but found them in food. 2. Didn't ask about spice level and it was so different on the two things we ordered. 3. Taste was pretty ok and we had doubts on quality on some veggies in the dish.
Food is always consistent and the service is great.

Yummy yummy food!!!!! This place serves the best crispy spring rolls!!! Very delicious food!! Also, they customize the spice level as per our choice. Amazing ambiance!  Appreciable service! The waitress was very very sweet! The food was irresistible to capture a picture😂  When in New Orleans definitely a must try!!

I was looking for Asian food restaurants in New Orleans. I tried several but need to have a bit spicy and hot dish. I found it in front of Hilton Hotel, but the taste was quite localized so the dish I ordered was not spicy for me. Staff were friendly and clean restaurant.
Closest thing to home after 4 days of being in NOLA.
Food was not bad but it was different compared to other Thai restaurants..
Good thai
Very slow service, good food. A smile can go a long way when you are in the service business!!!!
Just so so

Very unfriendly staff. They charge 20% tip to your bill without asking permission even if you're on your own (the menu states that 20% will be added for parties of 5 or more)! Unacceptable practice. I had them void my credit card charge and redo it but the waiter got into a verbal abusive fight with me.

Pretty legit Thai place with friendly service. The Tom yum soup was quite authentic. The dishes were less so but still decent. And prices were good. Not a bad find in New Orleans if you need your Thai fix.
Used to love singha. Had it today for the first time in a while. Pad Thai is basically noodles and ketchup. Lacked bean sprouts, basil and lime. It felt like freezer food.
Mediocre at best.
Average
Bad service with attitude :( but food was good :) they charged 20% before you even know it :(
Quick affordable lunch. Quick turnaround.

My husband and I were looking for something different here in NOLA and we love Thai food. We found this place. It was completely empty upon entering which concerned us a bit about how our dinner would go. However we were seated and our drink order was taken promptly. We noticed they do ALOT of take out. Which made us feel better about our expectation of the food. I had she fish panang special with extra veggies instead of rice. The fish was very bland but the sauce was flavorful. He had the shrimp basil and said it was good but not super yummy. Basically I get why the restaurant was empty in the crowded NOLA downtown area, but I also get why there were tons of take out orders. The food is definitely take out worthy
Great takeout!  Plenty of food.  Delicious!!
Nice food
Quick and Delicious
Food was wonderful experience,  very authentic.   The service was pleasant but not very attentive even though it was not very busy.
Nice food..

The food is excellent, I have tried several curries and the pad thai. There are many vegan/vegetarian options. That really is the only good piece I have to say. I have eaten here on three occasions either before, during, or after the lunch rush. Each time it was extremely difficult to get the attention of the waiter, even when the restaurant was nearly empty. Our water glasses were never refilled and the "clean" tables upon arrival were very sticky. The last time I went we sat in the nearly empty restaurant, around 1:30pm finished our food, and then waited with empty plates and glasses for 45 minutes. We tried several times to flag down other waitstaff not assigned to our table and were told that they couldn't do anything for us because they were not our assigned waiter. It was very unpleasant and we were late getting back to the office. But the food was delicious.

Pad thai tofu was mediocre - slapped together, flavorless.  I asked for spicy sauce and got Sriracha to sprinkle!  The restaurant was empty, but the guy seemed busy attending to something and the kitchen seemed to cook up a storm ,🤔 Poor service and disappointed. I love Thai.  Not this one.

Great Thai food.   Good service.  Many noodle and rice dishes.   From chicken to shrimp and more,  there plates are tasty and spiced food (when you compare to New Orleans food).   They do offer spice adjustment to dishes to tailor for your spicey palette.
New ambience with good vegetarian options
The flavors are great, and the serving sizes on point - of note, the pad see ew is exceptionally tasty, and the curries have great flavor. They know how to create sauces, here!
This place has a good variety of Thai dishes.  If you're working in the CBD, this is a great spot to dine in for a quick lunch. They have a lot of seating. I like the pad thai and spring rolls
Excellence. Got a soup made with coconut milk, forgot what it's called, it was unreal delicious. You can get lots of dishes made vegetarian, time of options. Highly recommended.
Great pad thai.

Poor service, Iam Thais and just visiting NOLA, everytime I visit Thai restaurant anywhere in the world, Thai smile and warm welcome always happen, but not this place.And worst they're Thai people too, I rather go to The Sukho Thai restaurant even the server is all Americans but Thai smile and warm welcome  existed. Food  is good too
Love the cashew chicken (I ask them to add a little spice). Can't speak for anything else. Ambience not so great. But on tastiness of the aforementioned cashew chicken: 4.5 stars.
Never had bad did here. Always awesome :)
Excellent food and reasonably priced.
Best Thai in the CBD and likely the East Bank.  Parking can be tough as they have no lot of their own.  Our go-to items are the pad thai and the panang chicken curry.
We ordered from Uber Eats... and it was delicious. Everything we ordered was full of pleasing flavors. When in the CBD, find this place!
Tasty Thai food in downtown
Their curry is to die for!!
The food was excellent. Came out fast. Great and friendly service. Chicken salad was fantastic. Great pad thai and Mee Grob. Mango and sweet rice desert was excellent.
Quick and delicious but not fast food
My favorite Thai restaurant in the city!
Great food tucked away in a little corner of New Orleans
I agree that for most places like this you should stay away from the Pad Thai (which is essentially American fast food) and go with more traditional food like the Penang curry which was excellent.
Best Pad Thai I have had in years,  very flavorful. Nice cozy restaurant.
The dumplings and the Penang Curry were excellent. My partner had a noodle dish which was quite bland, but overall we really enjoyed it.

Ordered the Shrimp Pad Thai and it was okay. It needs more sauce or flavoring as the noodles were dry. Portion size is definitely good for the price point, food was prepared quick and still hot by the time I received it, and they're on UberEats which is how I found this place. Maybe the other menu items are more flavorful, but I wouldn't order this particular dish again. I’ve had better from a local food truck.
Decent Thai food. Location is tucked away in Gravier street (right across the Hilton Garden Inn).
Consistent, quality food, and good service. Love the spring rolls most, but everything is good.
Good curry range and delicious satay.
Decent food and fairly priced. The service was friendly and the atmosphere was relaxed.
Very friendly service and fresh amazing food

Very very bland chicken pad thai. The quantity was generous but the dish had little to no taste. Had I not been stuck at the office and hungry I probably would have thrown it out. I would not recommend this place at all and I'm not a picky/particular person.
Not that great. Food was overly sweet.
Great Thai cusine.

The food was awful, I was extremely hungry and could not take more than 3 bites (And we ordered 4 dishes). I love Thai food and have tried almost every place in the New Orleans area, I wish I hadn't wasted my money trying this one.
Average food
Great lunch spot.  Love the curries or ginger fish.
Meh.
It's okay. And they charged 20% service fee, which does not necessarily represent the quality.
You can't go wrong with anything on the menu! Savory dishes at great prices served with a smile...awesome place♥️

Not the best Thai food, but it’s not bad either. Service is pretty good and the food comes fast, which makes it a pretty popular place for lunch. I want to like this place because it’s so close to where I work, but every time I come here, I can’t find something that I really like. I’ve been to Thailand and have been to a lot of Thai restaurants in the states, and the food here just doesn’t have a familiar taste. Many Americans would like the food here, but those familiar with real Thai food may find it disappointing. I will keep trying this place and will adjust my review if I find the right dish that really takes me back to Thailand.
Excellent food. Specially liked the Crawfish Vermicelli. Authentic like Thai food.
I've been a Singha fan for many years.

Food was decent but service was lacking. Never received a drink refill, and when coming to clear our plates the sever simply dumped our checks off instead of asking if we wanted dessert (which we did).

The place is usually crowded which I don't mind in downtown. Food quantity and ingredients are  sometimes inconsistent. Also, they have added couple of dollars in my bill few times which I don't get why. Other than that, good place for lunch. Great price in downtown.
Great food, terrific environment
Delicious and absolutely fresh Thai food with veggie options.
Absolutely the worst Tom kha soup I've ever had.  It had no season and hardly any vegetables. It was basically a can of coconut milk heated up.  Thanks for ruining my dinner.

I was staying at the Hilton Garden Inn so access to this restaurant is about as close as you can get. The food is excellent here and service is fast. Portions are not large though. Service is friendly and professional.
Food is good and reasonably priced! I had the Thai Tea and Pad Thai
Love the Pad Thai.
The duck was horrible
The calamari is excellent, the wine was good, and I got a thai tea with a shot of vodka at the server's suggestion. 10/10 would come again!
We could walk there from our apartment. We always got take out. We loved the pad Thai..
Delivery from Uber Eats
Excellent very accommodating to vegetarians​
Crispy Duck is wonderful!!!!
Great place for a quick bite for lunch
Love love love their spring rolls and pad thai.  They have the best carrot sauce in the city  =)
Authentic Thai food. Delicious!
Great thai food.

I come here all the time (even have their number saved in my phone) since I live right around the corner. I always order take out and it has been good food - never a problem. Tonight, I opened my pad Thai and noticed right away that I did not get the same portion as normal (for a $15 dinner I expect to get every bite of it). There were also not as many veggies or pieces of tofu. As I'm eating, I notice a piece of tofu with a greenish tint - which is so NOT normal. I've had this plenty of times and never got an off colored tofu. Disgusting!! I want to throw up!! Singha Thai has lost my business for sure.
Food was amazing.
Good food and service! I had the chicken panang curry and the serving size was very generous.
Best Thai food in the city!!!
Really great quality and flavor. Will absolutely come again!
Terrible.. beef was basically TV dinner quality. Coconut soup tasted like lemon juice, portions so small that it was insulting for the price. I would NEVER east here again. All around awful.

Go elsewhere for Thai. The service was rude (hung up on twice without questions answered) and the food is VERY bland. My noodles taste like nothing but oil was put on them. A major disappointment for what looks like a nice place.
Very good food, price, and place.
Great spot for Thai in the CBD. Also a good place to avoid crowds and a wait for dinner.
Excellent service and the Thai food is always fresh and so good. Works are as good as gold!!!!
But i am thailand

Terrible service, not very clean and food was even worse. My colleague wanted to try Thai. I just came back to the US from a 8-years work engagement in Bangkok. I know that it is hard to compare Thai food in Thailand with Thai food abroad but this was really a bad experience.

Extremely baad with "aa" We requested no spice, very mild but what they gave us blew our heads off... So spicy , red chilly flakes were visible. We came from NYC and we regularly eat thai food and believe me they know what is mild and what is spicy. I would rate it in minus...

Atmosphere: 3.  This is an Asian family-style restaurant that caters to the workers in the neighborhood. It's very casual. The online photos of the interior look better than the real thing. The outside was low key. It's not trying to catch the attention of people passing by. I suppose it could be interpreted as having confidence.  Service: 3. I came after the lunch hour rush, so I didn't have to wait for a table, just someone to acknowledge my presence :-[  No one came  forward to greet me, so I started to wonder if I was supposed to seat myself :- The person who finally showed me to a table appeared to be the only waitress on duty, so I guess it was good that the bartender took my order.  He was attentive, accommodating about a side order,  asked what I thought of  the food, and didn't keep me waiting for my bill :-)  Food: 3. Don't expect the food to be sublime. It's basic no-frills cooking. The dish presented had no carved vegetables nor finishing touches. I've had better and worse. If you crave a taste of Thai, it gets the job done,  Value: 3.5 Pricing was fair for both the food and service.
Excellent food for a reasonable price. Ginger vegetable and tofu dish was wonderful. Yellow curry with rice was very nice as well. Fine flavors. I would definitely fine there again.
Good food and fast service makes this a nice lunch spot.

Great Thai food! There are not many (if any others) Thai places near the CBD. So this one meets the need. You want to get here no later than 11:30  before it gets packed. Good pad thai. Musaman chicken plate. Well, everything I've tried here is good. Service is also good and speedy if you need to get back to work.
Pad Thai was too salty last time. Other than this, prior experiences have been ok
Delicious!! Great service and good price

Went here about 45 minutes before closing on Thursday night and was surprised at how busy it was.  Sat at the bar and was promptly greeted.  Very good Thai food (I had the Mint Garlic Basil Chicken) and I'll definitely be coming back.
The food was quite tasty! Just finished our meal - May 2016.

My wife and I stayed in the Hilton Garden Inn just across the street from this restaurant for one week and we never saw more than 5 people at any given time inside of this restaurant which made us feel a little wary to go inside and eat.
Great thai food, which is hard to find in this city
Great Curry!

Ordered the cashew nut chicken plate and it was pretty good. Gets pretty sweet towards the end, and they only give you 1 scoop of rice, had to order 2nd scoop. This was the only Thai restaurant around this area. Would I go back? Yeah, I guess, if I was in the mood for Thai again.
Wonderful food, great service. Owner/chef is best in the business.

Worst food(feeling awful after having couple of bites) and customer service. As per my opinion, I would not recommend this place to anyone. If you don't trust this honest opinion then please go ahead and try.

Delicious! We had the Ginger Fish and the Pad Ke Mow and would highly recommend these dishes (especially the Ginger Fish which is a deep fried tilapia) - very tasty and fresh. I guess every restaurant in New Orleans has to serve great food or else!
Very nice Thai food.  The mango salad is excellent, a perfect balance of flavors.  Fast service.
